<a name="SampleReportBuilding"></a>
<h3>Building a Somatic Report: An Example</h3>
<p>This section provides a walk-through of mapping from an example somatic report to FHIR using the structure definitions and guidance defined in this IG. A somatic report focuses on the implications of a patient’s genetics (generally the therapeutic implications of somatic variants). The somatic report is represented as a Genomics Report. The related observations and other resources are referenced by the report. The intention of this page is to provide a “User Guide”, based on a specific report example, highlighting how the defined profiles can be used together to encode important relations in somatic reporting.</p>

